  "title": "Production Support Analyst",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>•            Investigate production issues, respond based on production defect severity SLAs</p><p>•            Manage and respond to users on timely manner.</p><p>•            Log incident ticket for production issues and user queries</p><p>•            Follow up on defect and incident closure and meet incident closure KPI</p><p>•            Make sure system availability as per respective agreed SLA</p><p>•            Ensure daily start of day(SOD) and end of day(EOD) execution for supported applications complete successfully</p><p>•            Provide support for annual Disaster Recovery (DR) exercise for supported applications</p><p>•            Provide support to System Engineers on server level patches / upgrade as and when applicable</p><p>•            Knowledge with 3rd party monitoring tools like Control-M, Geneos, Splunk, SQL Monitor</p><p>•            Knowledge with Market Data, and Geneos monitoring setup and dashboard configuration</p><p>•            Ensure application incident & task documentation is properly updated for each production release</p><p>•            Enthusiastic, hardworking, proactive and goal-oriented, with excellent communication and presentation skills, demonstrated professionalism and attention to detail</p><p>•            Proven ability to work and resolve production incidents under strict time constraints and provide workarounds using AS400/mainframe or unix shell or DB scripts etc</p><p>•            Strong skills in AS400, Linux/Unix Shell scripting, MS SQL, Oracle, BMC Control-M Scheduler</p><p>•            Good to have understanding and experience of ITIL methodology [service operation]<br /></p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong><br /></p><p><em><strong>Education:</strong></em></p><ul><li><em>Bachelor’s Degree in Computer Science or a  related field.</em></li></ul><p><em><strong>Essential Skills & Experience:</strong></em></p><ul><li><em>Prior hands-on production support experience on </em><em><strong>Open Systems</strong></em><em> and/or </em><em><strong>AS/400</strong></em><em>.</em></li><li><em>Strong support knowledge in at least one of the following: </em></li><li><em>Retail or wholesale payment systems</em></li><li><em>Customer information systems</em></li><li><em>Batch monitoring </em></li><li><em>Monitoring tool – Splunk, Geneos</em></li><li><em>Willingness to work in an </em><em><strong>onsite shift-support model (24×7)</strong></em><em>.</em></li><li><em>Hands-on experience in: </em></li><li><em>Writing AS/400 and SQL queries</em></li><li><em>Parsing logs for issue investigation</em></li><li><p><em>Writing shell scripts (UNIX) to optimize incident investigation</em></p></li><li><em>Strong written and verbal communication skills; ability to manage user interactions effectively.</em></li><li><em>Ability to quickly adapt to new technologies and environments.</em></li><li><em>Minimum </em><em><strong>2 years of production support experience</strong></em><em> in banking or financial services across multiple\n       technologies/platforms.</em></li><li><em>Ability to work in a </em><em><strong>fast-paced, high-pressure environment</strong></em><em>.</em></li><li><em>Willingness to work across multiple platforms: </em><em><strong>UNIX/Open Systems, AS/400, and Mainframe</strong></em><em>.</em></li></ul><p><em><strong>Additional Considerations:</strong></em></p><ul><li><em>Candidates with experience in </em><em><strong>operations teams</strong></em><em>, </em><em><strong>batch monitoring</strong></em><em>, or similar roles in different\n       industries are also encouraged to apply.</em></li></ul><p>–</p><p>Skills <strong>: </strong></p><ul><li><em><strong>SQL</strong></em></li><li><em><strong>AS40</strong></em></li><li><em><strong>Control-M</strong></em></li><li><em><strong>Mainframe </strong></em></li><li><em><strong>Unix</strong></em></li><li><em><strong>Shell Script</strong></em></li><li><em><strong>Geneos</strong></em></li><li><em><strong>Splunk</strong></em><br /></li></ul>",
